<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-14T23:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-14T23:29:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1083</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-14T23:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February, 14, 1917—11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Publication of statement giving position of United States regarding
                            revolutions has had most clarifying effect upon public mind and the
                            Government officials deeply grateful.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
